text: Kuzminovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Pervomaysky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 251 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 38 km from Sterlitamak, 25 km from Pervomayskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Kuzminovka, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
